column1: Identify the two species that most frequently appear together within a single image
column2: You need to find out any two species which are found the most in a single image, so you need to combine the bounding_boxes and compare the image_id of the two species.
column3:
SELECT TOP 1
    bb1.concept AS species1, 
    bb2.concept AS species2, 
    COUNT(*) AS frequency
FROM 
    dbo.bounding_boxes AS bb1
JOIN 
    dbo.bounding_boxes AS bb2 
ON 
    bb1.image_id = bb2.image_id AND bb1.concept < bb2.concept
GROUP BY 
    bb1.concept, 
    bb2.concept
